# React UI

## Theme & accent

- Client theme: `ThemeProvider` uses `resolveThemeAccent(pathname)` from `config/app-theme.ts`
- Hub = `HUB_ACCENT_COLOR` (`gray`); apps = `red` \| `green` from `getAppThemeMeta`
- Decorative icons/links on marketing surfaces: Radix `var(--accent-*)`, not fixed palette colors per section

## When to use what

| Need | Component |
|------|-----------|
| Blog / FAQ / roadmap / feedback header | `SitePageHero` |
| Legal page title block | `AppLegalHero` → `SitePageHero` |
| Home or roadmap app promo | `HomeAppCard` + factory helpers |
| App landing feature sections | `LandingPrimaryGrid` (`featured` default; `panel` / `compact` for denser blocks) |
| Store / download CTA on landing | `LandingStoreButton` (not legacy `LandingHero`) |
| Contact strip | `AppContactCta` |
| Screenshots / marketing images | `OptimizedImage` |

## Landing grids

```tsx
<LandingPrimaryGrid variant="featured" … />  // metal cards + LANDING_SURFACE_GRID
<LandingPrimaryGrid variant="panel" … />     // bordered section
<LandingPrimaryGrid variant="compact" … />   // panel + compact density
```

Do not duplicate grid markup in `AppLandingPage` — add items to `config/landing-content.ts` and render via `LandingPrimaryGrid`.

## Utility pages

```tsx
<Container size="2" className="site-prose">
  <SitePageHero eyebrow="…" title="…" lead="…" />
  …
</Container>
```

Legal content stays in `components/legal/*Content.tsx`; shared chrome only, not six different hero layouts.

## Client components

Use `'use client'` only when needed (animations, pathname, forms). Keep serializable props; theme meta via `AppThemeMeta`, not component refs in config.

## Tests

After layout/token changes: `npm run build` and `npm test`.
